------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party dependencies
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project depends on, but does NOT vendor or copy, the following components.
Each is installed from its published package and used through its public API;
its source is not included in this repository.

HALO (halo-engine)
  - Project:  context-labs/halo  (https://github.com/context-labs/halo)
  - Package:  halo-engine on PyPI
  - License:  MIT
  - Used by:  src/ail/l3/ — the L3 recursive trace reviewer adopts HALO as the
              trace-specialized Recursive LM engine. AIL adds only a thin MLflow
              adapter (MLflow trace -> OpenInference/OTLP SpanRecord JSONL), a
              structured-verdict parser, and the reviewer/attachment glue. The
              HALO engine itself is an optional dependency (the `l3` extra),
              lazy-imported, and is neither vendored nor reimplemented here.

DSPy (dspy)
  - Project:  stanfordnlp/dspy  (https://github.com/stanfordnlp/dspy)
  - Package:  dspy on PyPI
  - License:  MIT
  - Used by:  src/ail/judges/alignment.py — the optimizer backend that MLflow's
              MemAlignOptimizer requires for judge alignment. AIL does not call
              dspy directly; it reaches it through MLflow's public
              mlflow.genai.judges.optimizers API. dspy is an optional dependency
              (the `align` extra), lazy-imported inside build_memalign_optimizer,
              and is neither vendored nor reimplemented here.
